<h1>One Month Minimum Stay<br>Corporate &amp; Vacation Rental Condo for Rent in Portland, OR</h1><h2>1 Bedroom, 1 Bath, 1 Floor, Single or Double Occupancy, No Smoking, No Pets<br>http://www.CormorantProperties.com</h2><hr size="1"> 

<p><b>Perfect for business or vacation, this one-bedroom, fully furnished condominium is in an unmatched downtown, riverfront location close to everything. <br><br>Enjoy the amazing views from the living room, bedroom and deck. <br><br>Tasteful, upscale amenities are provided with attention to detail. We've tried to think of everything to make you comfortable. The Perch is fully stocked with quality appointments, from the living room to the kitchen, bath and bedroom--everything you would expect in a well-furnished home.</b>

<h2>Price Includes:</h2>Reserved parking spot<br>All utilities<br>Full Cable TV with all pay channels and OnDemand<br>Blu-Ray player<br>Apple TV<br>200Mb Internet (usually over 100Mb wireless)<br>Full kitchen and laundry in unit<br>In-sink water filter <br>Printer/scanner (for limited reasonable use)<br>Iron and full size ironing board<br>Blow dryer<br>Coffee and tea makers<br>Binoculars<br>Cruiser bikes for short trips<br>Community hot tub, pool, barbecue and fire pit<br>


<h2>Details:</h2>The Perch’s urban location offers the best of both worlds, with unbeatable access to downtown Portland and the popular Pearl District, while still being right on the river. Walk or take one of the many forms of public transportation within walking distance to some of the best galleries, urban parks, restaurants and bars in Portland, or stay in for the evening and barbecue on the deck overlooking the river. <br><br>Go for a jog or take a Cruiser out for a spin on the paved path that crosses the river via multiple bridges and has 5+ miles of scenic viewpoints.  <br><br>Use one of the guidebooks or maps we've provided to explore the city or browse the links below with free Wi-Fi. The Pittock Mansion, the Chinese Garden, Saturday Market, the Rose Garden Arena, Washington Park, and great shopping are all close by. <br><br>Your rental comes with a reserved parking space, but you don't need a car to enjoy Portland. You can walk in any direction, from the riverfront path into Downtown or over to the East side, or from the pedestrian bridge into the Pearl. There's even a small convenience store onsite, and Whole Foods and Safeway are within walking distance.<br><br>

<h2>Rates, Reservations and Inquiries:</h2>View our website for rental rates and to make reservations or inquiries: http://www.CormorantProperties.com/ThePerch.html

<h2>Rental Policies:</h2>Minimum Stay of 1 month required. There will be a $500 security hold put on your credit card. Any damages to the condo or its contents will be charged to this credit card. No smoking and no pets. Priority given to longer stays. Reservations of less than 45 days subject to a cleaning fee. <br><br>

</p>    </section>

